SUMMARY:Sturtevant's Ski-Ya-Later Sale: Up to 50% Off Ski and SnowboardGear
DTSTAMP:20260306T002948Z
DTSTART:20260317T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:PNW skiers and snowboarders—spring is the smartest time to upgr
	ade! Sturtevant's (part of Christy Sports) is hosting the annual Ski-Ya-La
	ter Sale from March 6-29\, offering up to 50% off current-season skis\, sn
	owboards\, boots\, bindings\, apparel\, and more—perfect as spring storms 
	bring late-season conditions and families plan ahead during spring break.\
	n\nShop in-person at our Bellevue locations for expert tuning & repair\, c
	ustom boot fitting\, water sports rentals\, and more: Sturtevant's – 13131
	 NE 20th St.\, Bellevue\, WA 98005 (425.869.7669) Hours: Mon-Fri 10 am-7 p
	m\, Sat-Sun 10 am- 6 pm\n\nSturtevant's Ski Mart – 13219 NE 20th St.\, Bel
	levue\, WA 98005 (425.637.8958) Hours: Mon-Fri 10 am-7 pm\, Sat-Sun 10 am-
	6 pm\n\nOr head to Tacoma: Sturtevant's Ski Mart – 2220 So. 37th St.\, Tac
	oma\, WA 98409 (253.473.1134) Hours: Mon-Fri 10 am-7 pm\, Sat-Sun 10 am-6 
	pm.\n\nGreat for families: Stop by for kids' fit checks\, season rental in
	fo\, and early purchases before fall pricing. All discounted items are fin
	al sale\; selection varies by store. Also shop online at christysports.com
	 or sturtevants.com. Upgrade your gear locally this spring—visit Sturtevan
	t's Bellevue or Tacoma today.\n\nDates: March 6 – March 29\, 2026 (Progres
	sive discounts: Up to 30% off March 6-12 with the best selection\; up to 4
	0% off March 13-19\; up to 50% off March 20-29 for the deepest savings)\n\
	nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/sturtevant-s-ski-ya-later-s
	ale-up-to-50-off-ski-and-snowboardgear/18276036/2026-03-17T00\n\nFrom SEAt
	oday - Sports & Outdoors
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/sturtevant-s-ski-ya-later
	-sale-up-to-50-off-ski-and-snowboardgear/18276036/2026-03-17T00
LOCATION:Sturtevant's Ski Mart - Bellevue\, 13219 NE 20th St.\, Bellevue\, 
	WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-sports
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT8H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:bkweZAjMjr_ZVqjTAxE38
SUMMARY:TADAIMA: I'm Home
DTSTAMP:20260306T002948Z
DTSTART:20260317T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:After more than 80 years\, a treasured collection returns “home
	” to Seattle’s Japanese American community. In 1942 dozens of traditional 
	Boys’ and Girls’ Day dolls were entrusted to Bailey Gatzert Elementary Sch
	ool by Japanese American families facing forced incarceration. Most were n
	ever reclaimed after the war. Artist Miya Sukune uses recent research in M
	OHAI’s collection\, as well as interviews with Japanese American survivors
	 and their descendants\, to create an installation called “Tadaima\,” mean
	ing “I’m home.”\n\nTADAIMA: “I’m Home!” Bringing Seattle’s Girls’ and Boys
	’ Day Dolls Home reconnects the dolls with their traditional role of prote
	cting and blessing children. It invites visitors to celebrate the resilien
	ce\, memory\, and enduring traditions of the Japanese American Community.\
	n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/tadaima-i-m-home/18096356
	/2026-03-17T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/tadaima-i-m-home/18096356
	/2026-03-17T00
LOCATION:Museum of History and Industry\, 860 Terry Ave N\, Seattle\, Seatt
	le\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
